Package org.team1540.rooster.testers.motor

Class EncoderTester

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team1540.rooster.testers.AbstractTester<ChickenTalon,​Boolean>
      • org.team1540.rooster.testers.motor.EncoderTester
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sendable, Runnable, Tester<ChickenTalon,​Boolean>
    public class EncoderTester
extends AbstractTester<ChickenTalon,​Boolean>
implements Sendable
    Reports if an encoder appears to be non-functional by checking to see if a motor is running and if the corresponding encoder is moving.

      • testEncoder

        public Boolean testEncoder​(ChickenTalon controller)
        Tests to see if the encoder is working by checking to see if the controller is drawing more than 1 amp and if the selected ChickenTalon is moving at a velocity of less than 5.
        Parameters:
        controller - The ChickenTalon to test for burnout.
        Returns:
        Boolean indicating if the encoder is encoder has failed: true if it is suspected of failure, false if it is not suspected of failure.
